[Crim. No. 3255. In Bank. September 12, 1929.] In the Matter of the Application of J. W. MARSDEN on Habeas Corpus.

Herman A. Bachraek for Petitioner.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and Lionel B. Browne, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE' COURT.

— The application of the petitioner herein for relief upon habeas corpus is denied upon the authority of In re Haines, 195 Cal. 605 [234 Pac. 883], The writ of habeas corpus is discharged and the prisoner remanded.
